# Day 8 – Passwords + Account Lockouts (Help Desk Core)

## Completed:

- Reviewed Active Directory account lockout policies
- Examined the Default Domain Policy account lockout settings:
  - Account Lockout Threshold
  - Account Lockout Duration
  - Reset Account Lockout Counter After
- Modified the Account Lockout Threshold from **3 failed attempts** to **2 failed attempts** for lab testing
- Updated Group Policy by running **gpupdate /force** on both **DC01** and **Client01**
- Simulated a user account lockout using the **Pickles Pugsley (PnP)** domain account
- Verified the account was locked in Active Directory Users and Computers (ADUC)
- Unlocked the user account
- Verified the account was enabled and not disabled
- Confirmed the user was able to successfully authenticate after the account was unlocked
